spans.text: The Red Ribbon Express (RRE) is the world’s largest mass
mobilisation drive on HIV/AIDS. The train will travel
through 22 states, during its one year long journey, halting
152 stations. Through the RRE, NACO, intends to break
the issue of HIV/AIDS, by taking
the messages on prevention, care and support to people
living in small towns and villages across the country. The
aim is also to create an environment, free from stigma
and discrimination faced by people living with HIV, so they
can access the services, without fear and prejudice, and
It has proved to be a successful multi-
sectoral initiative, of the NACO and a po
tool, both at the state and district level, besides enhancing
local capacity to deal with HIV prevention.
